  "prompt": "Is there a feature length biopic on Albert Einstein? If not, why?",
  "response": "While there isn't a definitive, widely-released feature-length film solely about Albert Einstein's life, there have been several portrayals and TV movies:\n\n1. \"Einstein\" (2008) - A TV movie starring Andy Serkis, which focused on Einstein's life\n2. \"Genius\" (2017) - A National Geographic TV series starring Geoffrey Rush as Einstein, which covered much of his life\n3. \"I.Q.\" (1994) - A romantic comedy featuring Einstein as a character, played by Walter Matthau\n\nThe lack of a comprehensive, theatrical biopic might be due to several factors:\n- Einstein's life involves complex scientific concepts that are challenging to dramatize\n- His most significant contributions are theoretical and not easily visualized\n- His personal life, while interesting, might not have the dramatic arc typical of biopics\n- Rights and permissions for portraying his life could be complicated\n\nDocumentaries about Einstein are more common, as they can better explain his scientific work and historical context.\n\nWhile a definitive, big-budget Einstein biopic hasn't been made, his life and work have been explored in various media formats.",
